{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/bone-soft-tissue-sarcoma-recognition-referral/diagnosis/symptoms-suggestive-of-bone-soft-tissue-sarcoma/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"1f947dbd-c647-5adb-9201-f12c1c87035d","slug":"symptoms-suggestive-of-bone-soft-tissue-sarcoma","fullItemName":"Symptoms suggestive of  bone and soft tissue sarcoma","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 8a495104-79d8-442d-acdf-ca679dc9f10a --><h2>Symptoms suggestive of bone and soft tissue sarcoma</h2><!-- end field 8a495104-79d8-442d-acdf-ca679dc9f10a -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item ea46c8a7-596e-4435-a0e9-aa9ff8f2e4b4 --><!-- begin field 317b1f21-3a26-42b0-a32a-c3c29abaf5d6 --><p><strong>Table 2. </strong>Symptoms suggestive of bone and soft tissue sarcoma.</p><table data-table-id=\"5d714880-8ac8-4db9-91cc-acce014fa9d1\"><thead><tr><th colspan=\"1\">Symptom</th><th colspan=\"1\">Possible cancer</th><th colspan=\"1\">Referral recommendation</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"1\">Lump (unexplained) that is increasing in size in adults</td><td colspan=\"1\">Soft tissue sarcoma</td><td colspan=\"1\">Consider an urgent direct access ultrasound scan (to be performed within 2 weeks)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\">Lump (unexplained) that is increasing in size in children and young people<sup>1</sup></td><td colspan=\"1\">Soft tissue sarcoma</td><td colspan=\"1\">Consider a very urgent direct access ultrasound scan (to be performed within 48 hours)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\">Bone pain (unexplained) in children and young people</td><td colspan=\"1\">Bone sarcoma</td><td colspan=\"1\">Consider a very urgent direct access X-ray (to be performed within 48 hours)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"1\">Bone swelling (unexplained) in children and young people</td><td colspan=\"1\">Bone sarcoma</td><td colspan=\"1\">Consider a very urgent direct access X-ray (to be performed within 48 hours)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"3\"><sup>1</sup>Separate recommendations have been made for adults and for children and young people to reflect that there are different referral pathways. However, in practice young people (aged 16–24 years) may be referred using either an adult or children's pathway depending on their age and local arrangements.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"3\"><strong>Data from: </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/bone-soft-tissue-sarcoma-recognition-referral/references/\">NICE, 2015</a>]</td></tr></tbody></table><!-- end field 317b1f21-3a26-42b0-a32a-c3c29abaf5d6 --><!-- end item ea46c8a7-596e-4435-a0e9-aa9ff8f2e4b4 -->","topic":{"id":"e4747ecc-d17a-5e2c-bd0c-69fc109a74f5","topicId":"6f65762b-a612-4ce9-80e5-ee8cb24f6dde","topicName":"Bone and soft tissue sarcoma - recognition and referral","slug":"bone-soft-tissue-sarcoma-recognition-referral","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2020","chapters":[{"id":"edf8fdb6-68e6-5dac-916a-206d3893e4b8","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"0b6c5a9d-30a1-51f3-b16c-afbf78f00757","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"f18ae9ed-24b3-5a8f-b9fa-aabc10e5ced7","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"25f4d7d5-200e-50b1-b791-8478134bfee4","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"cee3f7fc-90f5-5bab-8b99-9ad854a538e7","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"69a11364-50c2-5893-ba48-bfc291fd9678","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"5941fcea-4bbf-5dbd-9c8b-4fffe5ff513c","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"82675336-6e84-5f8b-8ae2-b134dad3713d","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"04ecd3ef-a02c-5cfe-857c-97bed1748869","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"19da7d85-1a17-5d25-99b1-16680fb8dad5","slu